<p><i><b>Everything Bad Is Good for You: How Today's Popular Culture Is Actually Making Us Smarter</b></i> is a book by <a href="/wiki/Steven_Berlin_Johnson" title="Steven Berlin Johnson">Steven Berlin Johnson</a>. In the book, Johnson claims that <a href="/wiki/Popular_culture" title="Popular culture">popular culture</a> – and in particular <a href="/wiki/Television" title="Television">television</a> shows and <a href="/wiki/Video_games" title="Video games" class="mw-redirect">video games</a> – has grown more complex and demanding over time and is making us smarter.</p>
